        {
            "_id": "aafpuxt66c9n4wag",
            "data": {
                "actionCategory": {
                    "value": "offensive"
                },
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The sun-spire collects solar energy and uses the energy to create a deadly beam of fire. It fires the beam in a @Template[type:line|distance:120], dealing [[/r {11d8}[fire]]]{11d8 fire damage} to all creatures in the line (@Check[type:reflex|dc:33|basic:true] save). The concentrated beam ignites everything in its path, including the air, creating a wall of burning flame along the line that continues to burn until the end of the sun-spire's next turn. This wall has the effects of a 5th-level <em>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.Wall of Fire]{Wall of Fire}</em> spell, dealing [[/r {5d6}[fire]]]{5d6 fire damage} to any creature that crosses the wall or occupies the wall's area at the start of its turn. The sun-spire can't use the Beam of the Seven Suns again for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}, although rounds it's not in sunlight don't count toward this number.</p>"
                },
